The paper deals with the problem of consensus control for networks of nonlinear agents, which is a typical topic in the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of multi-agent systems and the load balancing application suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The stochastic environment and noisy measurements indicate that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The use of switching topology and incomplete information suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of analytical and simulation methods for performance evaluation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
